quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  84,1,"When the sky has split [open]"
  84,2,"And has listened [i.e., responded]{1} to its Lord and was obligated [to do so]",footnotes:1:1
  84,3,"And when the earth has been extended{1}",footnotes:1:1
  84,4,"And has cast out that within it{1} and relinquished [it].",footnotes:1:1
  84,5,"And has listened [i.e., responded] to its Lord and was obligated [to do so] -"
  84,6,"O mankind, indeed you are laboring toward your Lord with [great] exertion{1} and will meet it.{2}",footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  84,7,"Then as for he who is given his record in his right hand,"
  84,8,"He will be judged with an easy account"
  84,9,"And return to his people in happiness."
  84,10,"But as for he who is given his record behind his back,"